# Path 1 — SCE source of truth

When working on Pantheon **Path 1** (EE DMA/VIF1, VU1 / `shader.vsm`, XGKICK, GIF/GS semantics, alignment and hardware-facing details), treat **`C:\PS2Tools\sce\`** (Windows) and **`/mnt/c/PS2Tools/sce/`** (WSL, same tree) as the **source of truth** for manuals, headers, and official EE samples—not generic web answers alone.

Builds use **`PS2SDK`** from the environment; the SCE tree is the primary **documentation and reference-sample** authority when clarifying hardware behavior or Sony patterns.

Repo conventions and concrete path examples: [HANDOFF.md](../../HANDOFF.md) (section *Source of truth: official SCE tree (Path 1)*).
